KitKat:

She stoppped and growled at SharpClaw. "Look and listen. I don't give 
a damn about what emotions make you what. I do care about this. I 
will have the maximals stripped of thier metal skins, thier sparks 
pulled from thier writhing bodies and let thier scrap metal corpses 
rust out in the elements before my spark stops. Other than that, I 
need no emotions for anything else."  She turned and walked off 
again, this time, she started running. She'd be in the pit before she 
would let him see the tears running down her cheeks.

> SharpClaw: Hey there isn't a reason to leave. I'm sorry I struck a 
touchy subject. And dont tell me i sound like a Maximal. I am a 
Predacon, better then any Maximal. It does not make me a weak Maximal 
to live by emotions. It's how you react to them that really makes the 
difference between a Maximal and a Predacon.
